would have been a casualty for sure. Yeah. But I 
think it's affected everybody. It has. It sure

24:00.624 --> 24:01.204
has. All right. Has crime increased or decreased 
any? And has it affected you any? Well, I think

24:09.138 --> 24:11.041
crime is on the increase.

24:18.774 --> 24:21.719
Of course, we have more people now than we used to 
have. And we hear a lot more about it. It's

24:24.664 --> 24:25.886
publicized more. And people are able to get around 
more than they used to be. We used to have these

24:30.854 --> 24:35.061
hardtop highways and freeways. and 
farm-to-market roads and things like that, and

24:35.243 --> 24:38.930
they have good cars. Anybody can commit a crime in 
Brown and be in Houston in a couple hours and be out

24:40.172 --> 24:47.526
of the reach of officers. Because back in your day, 
we didn't have that. And in our days, we didn't have

24:49.670 --> 24:51.734
that kind of stuff. We just didn't know anything 
about it. And we have so much dope that's peddled.

24:57.805 --> 25:03.034
and everything till it just makes life more 
miserable, I think. Right. Did y'all have any

25:03.254 --> 25:06.039
horse stealing back in y'all's day? Well, we could 
have had. I don't remember any. Cattle hustling?

25:11.809 --> 25:13.332
Well, I'm sure we had cattle hustling. But I don't 
know. Where we lived, it was more of a community of

25:16.758 --> 25:22.868
people just all worked together. Right. Y'all 
didn't even have to lock your doors at night, did

25:23.551 --> 25:25.133
you? No, we never knew what it was to lock a door. 
Yeah, today you have to. And we ran off from any home

25:27.757 --> 25:29.639
we didn't lock our doors. Right. And if one person 
got into trouble that is needing some work done,

25:30.520 --> 25:38.411
got sick or something, all the community went and 
worked his crop out for him. Well, that's really

25:38.572 --> 25:39.112
great. If he's building a barn, they built a barn 
for him. And people just worked more in harmony

25:41.736 --> 25:45.702
then than they did now. They were more together. 
Yeah, more together. And more involved. That's

25:49.046 --> 25:49.327
right. Most people now don't want to get involved 
with anything. No, you're right there. They sure

25:51.810 --> 25:52.551
were. Well, has crime infected you any? No, the 
extent of just worrying, I think, is the only

25:57.029 --> 26:01.197
thing. You can't help but worry about youngsters. 
And I do have a bunch of young grandsons that are out

26:03.201 --> 26:11.196
at night and times like that and going to school and 
things. And that way, it helps. afraid something

26:13.507 --> 26:27.868
will happen to them, and that's about the only way 
it's affected me, because I keep my doors locked,

26:13.507 --> 26:27.868
and I'm in before night, and I don't get out after 
night unless I'm with some of the boys, or they come

26:13.507 --> 26:27.868
by to pick me up, take me somewhere. Have you had any 
bad casualties with your family? Well, yes, we had

26:33.176 --> 26:37.382
one terrible bad casualty. It is in 1918. At least I 
thought it was bad. It wasn't a fatal casualty, but

26:41.873 --> 26:46.328
my older brother had gone to the army. And he'd come 
home for Christmas holidays. And in the meantime,

26:50.040 --> 26:53.993
after he had left, we had built up a walk and we had 
fixed the brick along the side of it and this walk

26:54.327 --> 27:13.990
went out to this underground cistern and he didn't 
know it was there so the next morning he thought oh I

26:54.327 --> 27:13.990
think I'll just he told my sisters I think I'll just 
wake them all up with a Christmas gun so he took the

26:54.327 --> 27:13.990
shotgun out and raised it up to shoot it and he 
stumbled on one of these bricks and when he did he

27:15.083 --> 27:37.665
fell and naturally he stuck his hand out to catch 
himself and it blew all his hand off and he's lived

27:15.083 --> 27:37.665
with one hand all his life and then another one was 
my nephew my oldest sister's son was fixing to

27:15.083 --> 27:37.665
cross the railroad track here in Bryan and it was a A 
place where you couldn't see the train coming or

27:39.113 --> 27:42.142
anything. There was a lot of blockage there. And 
the garage sat right beside the track. And he

27:45.993 --> 27:47.798
started up on it. And as he did, the train hit him, 
hit the car. And it was weeks. We just didn't know

27:52.051 --> 27:53.595
whether he'd live or not. Oh, that's true. But I 
think prayers were some of the things saved him.

27:56.398 --> 27:57.479
The doctors gave him up. How bad off? I mean, was he 
really... He's fine now. Fine now. I mean, was he in

28:00.802 --> 28:02.824
intensive care when this happened? Well, then 
they didn't have intensive care. Oh, that's

28:04.306 --> 28:04.986
right. But he spent a long time ago there, so he 
married. And he has been teaching in the Air Force

28:08.750 --> 28:15.597
for years and years, ever since he graduated from 
A&M. And he's just doing fine. He's going to retire

28:17.539 --> 28:19.741
and come back here this year. And we'll be happy to 
have him home. Well, that's great.

